properties.headline: Blizzard Warning issued February 16 at 3:25PM AKST until February 18 at 6:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blizzard conditions expected. Total snow accumulations of
4 to 6 inches. Winds gusting up to 45 mph. Visibility will fall
to one quarter mile or less.

* WHERE...Kuskokwim Delta west of Bethel. Expect the worst
conditions along the Kuskokwim Delta coast.

* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to 6 AM AKST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Areas of blowing snow could significantly reduce
visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...There will be 2 parts to this storm as a
front moves over the Kuskokwim Delta Coast. Expect visibility
to drop to one half mile or less in blowing snow conditions
starting this evening. Part 2 will start early Monday morning
with the next front approaching the coast. Expect visibility
to drop to one quarter mile from Kipnuk to Hooper Bay at
times. The strongest winds will diminish Monday afternoon, but
expect snow and blowing snow to continue through the overnight
hours.
properties.instruction:
A Blizzard Warning means severe winter weather conditions are
expected or occurring. Falling and blowing snow with strong winds
and poor visibilities are likely. This will lead to whiteout
conditions, making travel very hazardous. If you must travel,
have a winter survival kit with you.

NWSheadline: BLIZZARD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM AKST TUESDAY WEST OF BETHEL
